                <h1>Understanding Background Knowledge: A Key to Learning</h1>
                <p>Background knowledge is the information and understanding a person already possesses about a topic. It forms the foundation for learning new concepts, allowing individuals to make connections, relate new information to existing knowledge, and enhance comprehension. Strong background knowledge is crucial for effective problem-solving and critical thinking.</p>
